Gove scores own goal after joke falls flat
Michael Gove has landed in hot water after using sports analogies to compare two neighbouring, prestigious schools.
The Education Secretary likened the independent schools to Tottenham Hotspur and Arsenal, causing umbrage at one of them.
While making a speech at Highgate School in North London, Mr Gove compared it to Arsenal, and drew a parallel between nearby University College School (UCS) and Spurs.
He reportedly said: “UCS might think it’s special but the glittering trophies go to Highgate. I can tell I’ve just lost about half the audience, but the right half to lose.”
